David Makhura says staff will not return to work until the building which caught fire this afternoon is declared safe. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng Premier David Makhura says staff at his office will receive counselling and will and not return to the building, which caught fire on Friday until it has been declared safe for work.The fire broke out on the top section of the building.While investigations are underway to determine the exact cause, it's suspected the blaze may have been sparked by an electrical fault.Makhura says the building must be safe before employees can return. The team that is here is going to go to every floor to make sure there s no other part of the building that is on fire. It was one of two fires that broke out at an office of the premier on Friday.A blaze ripped through the Eastern Cape premier's building in the afternoon.No one was hurt in that fire either.